  "local_port": 50834,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Why do clicks from Quora come up as direct traffic in my Google Analytics reports?",
  "response": "Clicks from Quora appearing as direct traffic in your Google Analytics (GA) reports can be attributed to how GA tracks and categorizes traffic sources. Here are the main reasons why this happens:\n\n### 1. **Quora's Use of HTTPS and Referrer Information**\n   - GA relies on HTTP referrer information to identify the source of traffic. However, when a user clicks a link from an HTTPS site (like Quora) to another HTTPS site (your website), the referrer information is passed. \n   - If the link is not properly tagged or if Quora strips or blocks the referrer information, GA may not detect the source and instead classify it as direct traffic.\n\n### 2. **Improperly Tagged Links**\n   - If the links from Quora to your website do not include UTM parameters (a common way to track campaign sources in GA), GA may not recognize the traffic source and defaults to categorizing it as direct traffic.\n   - Adding UTM parameters (e.g., `utm_source=quora`, `utm_medium=social`, etc.) to your links can help GA accurately attribute the traffic to Quora.\n\n### 3. **Traffic from Quora's App**\n   - If users click on links from Quora\u2019s mobile app, the referrer information might not be passed due to technical limitations in the app. This can result in GA classifying such visits as direct traffic.\n\n### 4. **Quora's Privacy Features**\n   - Quora (like many platforms) may implement privacy measures that prevent referrer information from being passed entirely. This can obscure the source of traffic in GA.\n\n### 5. **Manual User Behavior**\n   - Users might copy and paste URLs from Quora into their browser's address bar, bypassing the referral chain entirely. In such cases, GA will classify the visit as direct traffic.\n\n### How to Fix This Issue:\n1. **Use UTM Parameters**: Add UTM parameters to all links you share on Quora to ensure GA tracks the traffic correctly.\n   - Example: `https://www.yourwebsite.com/?utm_source=quora&utm_medium=social&utm_campaign=quora_promotion`\n2. **Check Quora\u2019s Referrer Policy**: Investigate if Quora is blocking referrer information and adjust your tracking strategy accordingly.\n3. **Monitor Mobile App Traffic**: If your audience is using Quora\u2019s mobile app, consider alternative tracking methods, such as promoting a unique landing page or using a URL shortener with tracking capabilities.\n\nBy properly tagging your links and understanding how referrer information works, you can ensure that traffic from Quora is accurately attributed in your GA reports.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
